We base the training of our entity embeddings on Wikipedia2Vec [25, 26]. Taking a knowledge graph as the input, Wikipedia2Vec extends the skip-gram variant of Word2Vec [18, 19] and learns word and entity embeddings jointly. The objective function of this model is composed of three components. The first component infers optimal embeddings for words W in the corpus. Given a sequence of words \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
