				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} \mathcal {L}_a = \sum _{e_i \in A} \sum _{w_o \in a(e_i)} \log \frac{\exp (\mathbf {V}_{e_i}^T\mathbf {U}_{w_o})}{\sum _{w\in W}\exp (\mathbf {V}_{e_i}^T\mathbf {U}_{w})}, \end{aligned}$$\end{document}where a(e) gives the previous and next c words of the referent entity e.

These three components (word context, link structure, and anchor context) are then combined linearly into the following objective function:4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
