				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} \mathcal {L} = \mathcal {L}_w + \mathcal {L}_e + \mathcal {L}_a. \end{aligned}$$\end{document}

Following the related work discussed in Sect. 2.3, we use the Tagme entity linker to identify the entities mentioned in the query. Given input query Q, we obtain a set of linked entities E(Q) and a confidence score s(e) for each entity, which represents the strength of the relationship between the query and the linked entity. We then compute an embedding-based score for every query Q and entity E:5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
